{"questionId":"21469","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A submarine is located in a sea at coordinates <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>−</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced></math> relative to a ship positioned&nbsp;at the origin <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>O</mtext></math>. The <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;direction is due east, the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> direction is due north and the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi></math> direction is&nbsp;vertically upwards.</p>\n<p>All distances are measured in kilometres.</p>\n<p>The submarine travels with direction vector <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The submarine reaches the surface of the sea at the point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the coordinates of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></math></strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">r</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext></math>&nbsp;</strong></em>has coordinates <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math><em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><br>Note:</strong> Accept the coordinates of <em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext></math></strong></em> in vector form.</p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21469","referenceCode":"21M.1.AHL.TZ1.13b.i","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the coordinates of P.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.12—Vector applications to kinematics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}